This paper deals with the development of a tool for building ontologies from XML schema files. Ontology building is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that involves creating a formal representation of knowledge in a particular domain. The use of XML schema files suggests a focus on data management and database systems (cs.DB), as XML is a common format for data exchange and storage. The paper also discusses methodology and tool requirements for ontology building, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the comparison to other ontology building tools suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) subcategories.
